  "text": "Where S (t) is the SI after administration of the contrast agent, and S0 is the observed SI when there is no contrast agent. T1, TE, and T2 denote the tissue longitudinal relaxation time, the echo time and transverse relaxation time, respectively [CITATION_1] .",
